# Steam native binaries and the local app id. Not committed on purpose: they are large,
# platform-specific, and licensed separately (steam_api64.dll comes from the Steamworks SDK), and
# steam_appid.txt is a local development detail rather than a property of the game.
#
# The game runs perfectly well without them -- models/steam.lua reports "not available" with a
# reason, and asynchronous build PvP needs no Steam at all. See docs/multiplayer.md for where each
# one comes from.
luasteam.dll
luasteam.so
luasteam.dylib
steam_api.dll
steam_api64.dll
libsteam_api.so
libsteam_api.dylib
steam_appid.txt
